https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/394438/linux-display-or-upgrade-security-updates-only-using-apt
https://access.redhat.com/documentation/en-us/red_hat_enterprise_linux/8/html/managing_and_monitoring_security_updates/identifying-security-updates_managing-and-monitoring-security-updates#displaying-available-security-updates_identifying-security-updates

- yum updateinfo list installed > /tmp/updatecheck.txt

- yum updateinfo
- yum updateinfo list updates security
- yum updateinfo list updates security --installed
- yum updateinfo | grep "Important Security"
	  	         | grep "Important Security"
			     | grep "Important Security"
- yum check-update
- yum list installed | xargs -n3 | column -t
			     
- apt list --upgradable
